						<summary>

						<p>States that Pōtaya, son of <hi rend="bold">Divākara-Peddēri</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Savviya-Shaḍaṅgavi,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Kommiya-Shaḍaṅgavi,</hi> gave fifty sheep each for the upkeep of perpetual lamps in the Vishṇu temple at <hi rend="bold">Valivēru.</hi> No date is given but it is presumed that this inscription belongs to the same year as No. 8.</p>						

						</summary>
